<subSubSection id="948823961ABADDFBB98B580187580045" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="21BF3739866481068F0CC0C0DCECC9DE" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">Distribution and ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3AB1D9B1D4701B824599464B28AD6E20" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">
Endemic to northern Mozambique where it is known from several localities on the eastern and southern shore of Pemba Bay (Baia de Pemba) near the city of Pemba where it occurs on heavy clay over coral-rag in coastal scrub at the upper margin of mangrove communities (
<bibRefCitation id="1FD00473E1D3A474B20B0BA05BCE94E2" author="Burrows, JE" journalOrPublisher="Adansonia" pageId="4" pageNumber="15" refId="B3" refString="Burrows, JE, Burrows, SM, Loetter, MC, Schmidt, E, 2018. Trees and shrubs Mozambique. Print Matters (Pty) Ltd, Cape Town." title="Trees and shrubs Mozambique. Print Matters (Pty) Ltd, Cape Town." year="2018">Burrows et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
); ca. 10 m alt. According to Rulkens (personal communication), Ernst Schmidt observed the shrub between Macomia and the coast in 2009 but later discovered the plant had been cut down. Rulkens also observed additional locations with many plants about 10 km from Pemba in small patches of coastal forest on fossil coral substrate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B97BBE0A7465E6E0D36B46227B64666A" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="14" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" type="threats">
<paragraph id="2B63B29C09143A669BC2E29650A95E21" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">Threats.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="56103AA5DD77D951D583AAD6EB107540" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="14" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicName id="F36DC4E5B1A219197289813D112C8A69" authorityName="Dorr" authorityYear="2018" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Eriolaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eriolaena rulkensii" order="Malvales" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rulkensii">
<emphasis id="C0AAF52E25F6F31D34715AFA9A138CC4" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">Eriolaena rulkensii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is exploited for firewood (fide 
<emphasis id="E9C23A8058437153D5E49CB75CDFB9B9" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">Rulkens 1</emphasis>
, in sched.) and, on a different scale, it is threatened because the coastal forests and woodlands of northeast Mozambique are subject to increased development following the instability resulting from the independence and civil wars (
<bibRefCitation id="5DEC50A837E4E77479771380FCCE8054" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5091/plecevo.2011.539" author="Timberlake, J" journalOrPublisher="Plant Ecology and Evolution" pageId="4" pageNumber="15" pagination="126 - 137" refId="B12" refString="Timberlake, J, Goyder, D, Crawford, F, Burrows, J, Clarke, GP, Luke, Q, Matimele, H, Mueller, T, Pascal, O, de Sousa, C, Alves, T, 2011. Coastal dry forests in northern Mozambique. Plant Ecology and Evolution 144 (2): 126 - 137, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5091/plecevo.2011.539" title="Coastal dry forests in northern Mozambique." url="https://doi.org/10.5091/plecevo.2011.539" volume="144" year="2011">Timberlake et al. 2011</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="9D74878A9629084852C4A689945FD03B" authorityName="Dorr" authorityYear="2018" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Eriolaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eriolaena rulkensii" order="Malvales" pageId="2" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rulkensii">
<emphasis id="4E5E224EDC15E58007E8DF25F2954054" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="13">Eriolaena rulkensii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is 
<pageBreakToken id="D1DDA53E62F1625DC6505780B35BE93F" pageId="3" pageNumber="14" start="start">only</pageBreakToken>
one of many new species discoveries and new records from the Cabo Delgado area of Mozambique, others of which are enumerated by 
<bibRefCitation id="4F20FE2E77055F8B8E156C6ECBBBEF5A" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5091/plecevo.2011.539" author="Timberlake, J" journalOrPublisher="Plant Ecology and Evolution" pageId="4" pageNumber="15" pagination="126 - 137" refId="B12" refString="Timberlake, J, Goyder, D, Crawford, F, Burrows, J, Clarke, GP, Luke, Q, Matimele, H, Mueller, T, Pascal, O, de Sousa, C, Alves, T, 2011. Coastal dry forests in northern Mozambique. Plant Ecology and Evolution 144 (2): 126 - 137, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5091/plecevo.2011.539" title="Coastal dry forests in northern Mozambique." url="https://doi.org/10.5091/plecevo.2011.539" volume="144" year="2011">Timberlake et al. (2011)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
